OL,6, Teletext was a very significant part of
OL,7, my growing-up. We got our first        
OL,8, teletext TV in Nov 1987, to replace an 
OL,9, irreparable Philips G8 Colour TV.      
OL,11, All I knew about teletext was the in-  
OL,12, vision broadcasts on BBC2. My brother  
OL,13, showed me how to interact with teletext
OL,14, through page numbers and I was wowed.  
OL,16, Later I discovered subtitles on page   
OL,17, 888. Speech-to-text amazed me. This    
OL,18, helped to improve my reading, writing, 
OL,19, spelling and grammar at school. I even 
OL,20, modelled my handwriting by the teletext
OL,21, characters.                            
