OL,6, Somehow I was influenced that Oracle   
OL,7, was the better service than Ceefax.    
OL,8, Back then you were either a Children's 
OL,9, ITV or BBC viewer.                     
OL,11,C"Wow! How did you do that?!"           
OL,12, My party trick was knowing all the page
OL,13, by heart, as quizzed intensively by my 
OL,14, brother's mates (I thought I was 'just'
OL,15, clever). I knew even Oracle's hidden   
OL,16, test pages.                            
OL,18, Televox is another story. Dad never    
OL,19, worked out why his phone bill once was 
OL,20, suddendly expensive and to this day    
OL,21, he still doesn't know (is it time?)    
